# Godot 2D Rules

See `docs/ai-rules.md` for full AI contributor guidelines.

- **Strictly 2D.** Never introduce 3D nodes, 3D physics, or 3D workflows.
- **Godot-native 2D.** Prefer built-in 2D solutions.
- **2D nodes.** Use Sprite2D, AnimatedSprite2D, Area2D, CharacterBody2D, CollisionShape2D, TileMap, AnimationPlayer, ParallaxBackground, ParallaxLayer when appropriate.
- **Separate visuals from logic.** Keep visuals and gameplay logic separate where possible.
- **Modular scenes.** Keep scenes modular and reusable.
- **Scripts.** Avoid scripts on passive visual assets; attach only when interaction or behavior is required.
- **Validate.** Run the project and verify scene changes before concluding a task.
